   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit_2">
    <property name="enabled">
     <bool>false</bool>
    </property>
    <property name="geometry">
     <rect>
      <x>560</x>
      <y>210</y>
      <width>431</width>
      <height>471</height>
     </rect>
    </property>
    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">
    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }

</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;From the time Jose Rizal left the Philippines for Europe in 1882, his intellectual journey evolved significantly. Initially driven by personal goals of education and professional development, Rizal soon became deeply immersed in the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Philippine reform movement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, advocating for reforms that would improve the lives of Filipinos under &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Spanish colonial rule&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;. This period of his life marks the transition from an academic and aspiring professional to a revolutionary intellectual—someone who would inspire national change through &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;literature&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;activism&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;philosophy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; dir='rtl' style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; line-height:138%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Rizal's advocacy, deeply rooted in his experiences as a student abroad, evolved through a series of groundbreaking works and public actions. By the early 1890s, he had become a key figure in the movement for peaceful reform, using his intellectual talents to challenge the colonial status quo. His writings, particularly his two novels, served as pivotal instruments in inspiring Filipinos to question the oppressive colonial system and to demand &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;social change.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
